베란다로 나가보면 더욱 더 와이드한 바다를 볼 수 있습니다.
취사가 안뒤지만 바다전망을 비롯 호텔식침구와 늘 같은 컨디션을 유지하기 위해 매일같이 방역과 청소에 심여를 기울이고 있습니다.
원룸형이지만 통유리를 통해 개방성이 좋습니다. 테라스까지 있어 문을 열었을때 길 하나 건너편의 바다가 너무 가까이 보이며, 바다전망이 저희의 가장 큰 자랑이기도 합니다.
취사도구는 없습니다만 간단한 조리를 할 수 있도록 전자렌지가 있습니다. 주변에 맛집이 너무 많고 공항주변에서 휴식이 아닌 관광을 목적인 분들에게 특히나 적합한 공간입니다.
냉장고는 일반 원룸형공간들보다 넉넉하게 냉동까지 같이 할 수 있는 소형냉장고를 마련하였으며 쇼파와 테이블까지 준비해놓았습니다.
욕실 어메니티는 샴푸를 비롯 비누와 바디워시와 치약등을 준비해놓았습니다.
통유리 밖으로 보이는 오션뷰입니다. 바로 앞 용담해안도로가 보이네요.
용담해안도로의 끝자락, 뒷공간에서 바다를 보며 촬영한 사진입니다.

Just one of the many areas for relaxing and taking it easy.  Glamping is supposed to be comfortable and full of unique, little luxuries - and we endeavour to make you stay here as special as possible.
Sieku has breath-taking views over local, private conservancies, Mukogodo forest, the Mathews mountains and sacred Mount Olokwe.

A typical tent set-up inside and out at Sieku Glamping.  All tents now come with a full waterproof and shaded porch, with stone floor (no mud on rare, wet days), deck chairs and lounge sofas, jiko fires to warm you in privacy while watching the stars.  We are full of little touches and many of them recommended as great additions by guests that we have incorporated into what we do and offer.
Glamping with a big view north!  This is the bottom garden and view that you will have all to yourselves
Inside the larger 5m and 6m tents.  We take a lot of pride on the small but important attention to details...
Each of our bells tent is luxuriously equipped, with comfy double beds and feather duvets, hand-crafted furniture, beautiful carpets and sheepskin rugs, and freshly cut flowers from the garden.
The beautiful Touareg Ultimate tent - with front and back doors and with beautiful, large windows that allow to enjoy the big views even more
Inside the brand new Touareg Ultimate tent, with double bed, feather duvet, pillows and cotton sheets etc
More big views over the back of Ngare Ndare forest and Lew conservancy
Each tent has a beautiful, outdoor and open-air bathroom and toilet.
Each bathroom has a large safari-style shower, with loads of hot water.
One of the little ensuite loos - all beautifully hidden away and with loads of special little touches
All tents have freshly cut flowers and beaded, recycled water bottles
The night skies at Sieku are usually incredible - either with the full moon or with skies full of stars and little light pollution
Around the tents and the main mess tent are fires and comfy safari chairs where many guests spend a lot of time enjoying the stars and hearing lions on the plains below
Our main sitting room is large and comfy, with plenty of books and games, and cosy fire heaters for cold nights.

Sieku's kitchen is full equipped with everything you need, including a two-ring stove and three level oven for family roasted dinners, bespoke- made butchers block and so on (oh and with magnificent views from the kitchen to Mount Kenya).
It's all about the small details.
Our kitchen is full of hand-crafted pottery
Our dining room is full of locally crafted, beautiful crockery and glassware, and a large log fire (with free wood) for long, cosy family dinners.
A typical dinner table set up.
Cosy nights with family and friends around the dining table lit with only candles, lanterns and a large fire
One of the breakfast tables in the top garden - with bid views of Mount Kenya behind
Sieku is a perfect place to come and relax and unwind.  We have several spots around the camp for quiet times and taking it easy.
Some of the tents also have hanging day beds for private use.

Are there any petanque (French boules) courts with such fine views?  Our very nice Jacques petanque set is always ready for guests.  It's an especially fun game to play with friends and sundowners in the late afternoon.  Enjoy!
There are several sheltered picnic tables hidden around the camp, which are perfect to work from, have a quiet cup of good coffee or for picnics and barbecues with friends
Each tent has a gorgeous, ensuite eco-loo.
All ensuite bathrooms come with locally-made and organise soaps, wash, shampoo, conditioner and body lotions.
Staying at Sieku Glamping means that the small things in a stay are as important as the big things.  Just some of the little details in one of the outdoor bathrooms
And some more small bathroom details - with seeds and shells collected from the Kenyan coast
The blue pools in the Ngare Ndare forest truly are the most incredible natural swimming pools in all of Kenya - and the forest is only 3kms from Sieku.

The Ngare Ndare forest is a UNESCO World Heritage Site.  It is an important part of Kenya's elephant migration route, and overlooks Lewa conservancy.  On the canopy walkway you can often see elephants and other game below you.
Just one of the many gorgeous waterfalls to explore and swim in in the Ngare Ndare forest
This beautiful, spring-fed river runs all the way through the forest creating a series of pools and falls.
The views from the top of the waterfalls are equally as beautiful as from below.
The Mukogodo forest is also nearby and this offers some of the finest views of northern Kenya - and these are perfect for adventures, picnics and sundowners.

The base camp at sunrise with its three platforms hidden away in the rainforest.
We will bring you this close to the camp with our 4x4 Jeep.
The observation platform on the right, sleeping platform on the left and two showers and toilets in between.
From our main platform you get awesome views into the jungle - an excellent spot for birdwatching.
There is running water on the camp, but no electricity or phone - also not internet, which can be a bliss for a change. ;)
...however most guests prefer to shower at the waterfall - which is just 5 minutes from the camp.
Also nearby is this beauty of a waterfall named Volio. It has been the scene of Hollywood productions too.
The night in the rainforest is spectacular, romantic and for some even a bit scary. On clear nights you have an excellent dark-sky site!
From the base camp you can take daytime excursions though our vast forests.
Get your wanderlust on - there are miles and miles of trails to be explored.
Sloths are frequent. They're well camouflaged but easy to observe once spotted.
Snakes are there, but difficult to see unless you actively look for them.
Different types of frogs are more or less visible depending on the weather.
You will find different weird plants every day you look for them.
There are also big flowers in the forest. This one is called Torch Ginger.
This Ceiba is said to be among the very biggest trees in Costa Rica.
Natural pools are all over the reserve - some of them big enough to take a swim.
Finding a good spot for the sunset is worth a short hike. :)
A good morning hike guarantees an equally relaxing siesta.
All platforms are interconnected because - yes - it does sometimes rain in the RAINforest.
We have knowledgable guides to teach you about the rainforest in English, Spanish and German.

Plenty of fridge and freezer space to keep your snacks or meals in. If you need a crock pot or any sort of kitchen equipment and if we have (likely do since we are a bakery) let us know and we will have it ready for you!

Relax in the welcoming seating area with a great view of the 65” television, the wood-stove or the beautiful outdoors. Right next to our selfie station complete with a vintage saddle and leather chaps!

Selfie station complete with a vintage saddle, spurs, and chaps, vintage hats, or wall artwork.

Just minutes from the slopes of Mt. Spokane, snowmobiling or cross country trails (even on the property) be cozied up in front of  the warm wood fire. We keep the home fires burning for you! With naturally downed trees.
Peaceful scenery surrounds this property, this is the view from inside the kitchen looking north. These are the doors you will enter the property through when you arrive.
Enjoy the evening roasting marshmallows, making s'mores by the fire pit.
So many places to relax and enjoy a meal. Pictured is our cozy breakfast table, perfect for enjoying the western view from the table while enjoying your morning coffee or playing board games.
Winter, Spring, Summer, and Fall! Each and every season is filled with wildlife! Drink your morning tea or coffee while watching the wildlife from your bed, coffee bar, or outside on the cozy porch.

Private entrance leads to your home-away-from-home! Witness every season,  Spring blooming colors; Summer warms the bones as the blue lakes sparkle; Fall's golden leaves usher in Winter. The white snow covered trees and fields melt away to spring.

Stay in our spacious park-like 10 acre modernized facility located in the beautiful PNW (Pacific Northwest) in Spokane county,  just minutes from Idaho and Washington lakes, rivers, ski areas, hiking, state and federal parks.
The property is home to a small business bakery, don't worry no employees will bother your stay and they do not share your space! Meet Rj one of the hosts!
The property’s large dining table can comfortably seat 12. The host has it set up for 10, the host is happy to provide more chairs if needed.
Entry to the bathroom, for privacy there is a lock on the inside.

Bathroom: view of the water closet and entry to the  mermaid named  tile in the shower. .

Bathroom: Water closet with a fully functioning American style toilet, thus the toilet paper is made available at all times.
Bathroom: Shower, with a 7 phase shower, overhead rain shower, body sprays, and hand wand. Use the hand wand to clean up and/or use it on  your fur family member!

Enjoy cleaning up in our spacious 7 point accessible shower. Beautiful modern rustic tile and fixtures provides plenty of space, comfort, and hot water. Our spa-like shower refreshes after a day on the mountain. Even wash-up your dog!

Interior view from the loft looking down is the wood stove, #2 & #3 rooms. There are steep stairs leading up to the loft. View the beautiful outdoors when the large lift door is open. The host opens the large door for you or show you how.
Loft with views! Lay in the luxury king bed and enjoy a cup of local organic coffee freshly made from the Breville coffee machine.

Loft with the King sized bed dressed with fresh bedding awaits each guest. The luxury pillow-top mattress and 100% cotton sheets are the perfect spot to rest after enjoying all the adventures this property has to offer.
View coming up the very steep stairs to the loft. It’s worth the climb!

#2 from inside the room with the room's French Doors and curtains both closed for privacy.

BBQ anyone? The host supplies the BBQ and tools and you supply the fun!
Outdoor patio seating next to the gas BBQ.

Enjoy a peaceful setting in the beautiful PNW (Pacific North West). Our ten acre small farm welcomes kids  + friendly dogs. Our dining table seats 10 or choose outdoor seating options, near the fire-pit, in the meadow, or nestled in the trees.

Enjoy life like a farm kid and take a swim in our tough pool near the open air fire pit. We provide the fire starting and will help with s’more if you’d like! We provide all you need for  roasting marshmallows or hot dogs!

Summer is one of our favorite seasons and you'll love it too! There are 76 lakes in Spokane county and we are less than an hour from any of them! Plus take the beautiful drive up HWY 2  to the sandy beach in  Sandpoint, Idaho and  Lake Pend Oreille.

Dog friendly! Do you have a friendly dog(s). We love dogs! Come stay with your best fur family members so they can enjoy the great outdoors with you! For an extra fee we are  happy to provide doggie daycare if you need to getaway without fido!

On the property enjoy numerous plant species, trees like majestic Tamarack and Pine trees.  Take selfie's from the natural granite  boulders  left by a large glacier which formed the area and our beautiful 10 acres.

Enjoy the half mile walking or cross country ski trail that rounds out the property. The trail is gentle, no hills only a gentle slope. The property is filled with wildlife like deer, wild turkeys, so please keep your dogs on a leash.
Peace and tranquility are found daily here. The sunsets are breathtaking. Our serene setting will help you re-center, gain appreciation for quiet and the most luxurious gift of all, nature.
Careful where you step! Nature is everywhere!

Swim or ice skate free on the local lakes including Bear Lake (pictured) less than 6 mi.   Deer and Eloika Lake under 8  miles away. We are less than an hour from Loon, Diamond, Liberty Lake, Lake Pend Oreille, Lake Ceour d' Alene,  and many others!

The 10 acre  farm is  home to  domestic chickens and wild turkeys.  Farmer Evan will teach about our organically fed hens. If  you are lucky we may have some chicks during your stay! Farm Fresh Eggs are available daily!

We have some beautiful spoiled hens who will be laying you some fresh eggs every single day! We will set these out for you to make your own breakfast or if you choose we will teach you how to make the best PNW egg frittata!
Our chickens are mostly friendly but most will run from you since they do t know you. If you want to pet or hold one we will help you pick the right hen, check out our Experiences!
Ski Schweitzer or Mt. Spokane or  Cross country ski our half-mile winter wonderland trail. Located near numerous State and Federal parks like Spokane Ski & Snowboard Park (approx 34 min drive).
Drive north up HWY 2 and in  just minutes you are at Diamond Lake. The pristine lake is one of the best for swimming and water sports!
Visiting for a wedding or other event? This large stainless steel work table is perfect for prepping large meals, creating flower arrangements, and so much more!
